# Normalize line endings to LF in the repository regardless of what a given
# editor/OS wrote on disk. Production (Linux) and local dev (Windows) had
# drifted onto different EOL conventions for the same unchanged files, which
# showed up as full-file diffs with no real content change — this setting
# plus `git merge -X renormalize` collapses those back to zero-diff merges.
* text=auto eol=lf
